  <steps>
    <step order="1">Grep for `LegalWorkspaceApp` mount hook + tab-selection logic to confirm integration point</step>
    <step order="2">If LegalWorkspaceApp is correct surface, identify the mount useEffect or initial state hook; otherwise document actual shell in notes/ and adjust target</step>
    <step order="3">Read `autoPopup` preference from preferences store (same source widget reads from)</step>
    <step order="4">On mount, if `autoPopup === true`, set selected tab to Daily Briefing (use existing tab-selection mechanism — do NOT introduce a new API)</step>
    <step order="5">Ensure behavior only fires on first mount, not on every render (use useEffect with empty dep or once-only ref)</step>
    <step order="6">Add Jest test: mount LegalWorkspaceApp with autoPopup=true → assert Daily Briefing tab is active; with autoPopup=false → assert default behavior</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm test`; ensure all pass</step>
    <step order="8">Run `npm run build` to confirm TypeScript compiles</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md ✅</step>
    <step order="10">Document the chosen integration point (and any deviation from spec assumption) in notes/</step>
  </steps>
